      "index": "g0342",
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "frameId": null,
      "text": "★ The same fact, eight costumes — and one trust boundary",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "★ The same fact, eight costumes — and one trust boundary",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "p1215-0344",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 54,
      "y": 11814,
      "width": 2448,
      "height": 39,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1f2937",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1746316800000,
      "index": "g0343",
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "frameId": null,
      "text": "• Stages 1–3 are CLIENT: the topping is a rich object, then collapses to a bare id on the wire. The browser's name/price are display-only and thrown away at the boundary.\n• Stage 5 is the TRUST BOUNDARY: the server re-resolves the id against its own catalog, so a tampered client price can't survive. From here the value is server-owned.\n• Stages 6–8 are FROZEN HISTORY: the JSON snapshot is immutable order history — even if 'Nhân thịt' is later renamed or repriced, this order still reads ₫0 'Nhân thịt'. (And note: it's a topping, never a 'filling' column.)",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "• Stages 1–3 are CLIENT: the topping is a rich object, then collapses to a bare id on the wire. The browser's name/price are display-only and thrown away at the boundary.\n• Stage 5 is the TRUST BOUNDARY: the server re-resolves the id against its own catalog, so a tampered client price can't survive. From here the value is server-owned.\n• Stages 6–8 are FROZEN HISTORY: the JSON snapshot is immutable order history — even if 'Nhân thịt' is later renamed or repriced, this order still reads ₫0 'Nhân thịt'. (And note: it's a topping, never a 'filling' column.)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
